article.description: Julian DeBose had a season-high 20 points, Antravious Simmons had 17 points and 10 rebounds and Florida Gulf Coast defeated La Salle 86-77 on Thursday.
article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast holds off La Salle 86-77
article.linkText: Florida Gulf Coast holds off La Salle 86-77
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Julian DeBose had a season-high 20 points, Antravious Simmons had 17 points and 10 rebounds and Florida Gulf Coast defeated La Salle 86-77 on Thursday. Marc Eddy Norelia added 15 points and nine rebounds for the Eagles (7-7), who outrebounded the Explorers 39-29. FGCU is 7-0 when it wins the boards. Cleon Roberts was 10 of 14 from the field for a career-high 30 points and Jordan Price had 25 for the Explorers (4-6). Florida Gulf Coast built a 19-point lead behind Simmons' 12 points in the first half but the Explorers shot 55 percent and Price scored 19 points in the second half to keep it a game. Price had a 3-point play with 5:51 left to cut it to six but DeBose quickly answered with a 3-pointer to start an 8-0 surge. Norelia had 12 points and Zach Johnson had all 10 of his points in the second half for the Eagles.
